    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Alliance
    The Alliance enum represents the two player alliances in a game of chess: White and Black.
    AlphaBeta
    The AlphaBeta class implements a chess engine using the alpha-beta search algorithm with Lazy SMP parallel search optimization.
    AlphaBeta.MoveSorter
    The MoveSorter enumeration defines different strategies for ordering moves to improve alpha-beta search efficiency.
    AlphaBeta.SearchStats
    The SearchStats class tracks performance statistics for individual search threads during parallel search operations.
    AlphaBeta.StripedTranspositionTable
    The StripedTranspositionTable class implements a thread-safe transposition table using striped locking to reduce contention in parallel search operations.
    Bishop
    The Bishop class represents a bishop chess piece that moves diagonally across the board.
    BlackPlayer
    The BlackPlayer class represents a chess player controlling the black pieces.
    Board
    The Board class represents a chess board containing 64 tiles and chess pieces.
    Board.Builder
    A builder class for constructing instances of the Board class with specific configurations.
    BoardEvaluator
    The BoardEvaluator interface defines the contract for evaluating chess board positions.
    BoardTransition
    The BoardTransition class represents the result of a move execution on the chessboard.
    BoardUtils
    The BoardUtils class provides utility methods and constants for working with a chess board.
    DebugPanel
    The DebugPanel class represents a specialized panel for displaying debug information and messages.
    EndgameBoardEvaluator
    The EndgameBoardEvaluator class provides specialized evaluation functions for chess endgame positions.
    engineDriver
    The engineDriver class serves as the main entry point for the Capstone chess engine application.
    EvaluationCache
    The EvaluationCache class provides a thread-safe cache for chess board evaluations to avoid redundant calculations during search operations.
    EvaluationCache.CacheKey
    The CacheKey class represents a composite key for the evaluation cache, combining a board's Zobrist hash value with the evaluation depth.
    GameHistoryPanel
    The GameHistoryPanel class displays the move history of the game in a table format.
    GameSetup
    The `GameSetup` class represents a dialog for configuring game setup options using Java Swing.
    GameStateDetector
    The GameStateDetector class provides precise identification of the current chess game phase and selects the appropriate evaluation function based on comprehensive position analysis.
    GameStateDetector.GamePhase
    Enumeration representing the three phases of a chess game.
    King
    The King class represents a king chess piece with specialized movement and castling capabilities.
    Knight
    The Knight class represents a knight chess piece.
    MiddlegameBoardEvaluator
    The MiddlegameBoardEvaluator class provides comprehensive position evaluation specifically tuned for middlegame positions in chess.
    Move
    The Move class represents a move in a game of chess.
    Move.AttackMove
    The AttackMove class represents a move that results in attacking an opponent's piece in chess.
    Move.CastleMove
    The CastleMove class represents a move that involves castling, which is a special king and rook move.
    Move.KingSideCastleMove
    The KingSideCastleMove class represents a move for king-side castling in chess.
    Move.MajorAttackMove
    The MajorAttackMove class represents a major attack move in chess.
    Move.MajorMove
    The MajorMove class represents a standard major move in chess.
    Move.MoveFactory
    The MoveFactory class provides factory methods for creating different types of moves.
    Move.MoveStatus
    Represents the possible outcomes of a chess move, including successful execution, an illegal move, or leaving the player's king in check.
    Move.NullMove
    The NullMove class represents a placeholder for no move in a chess game.
    Move.PawnAttackMove
    The PawnAttackMove class represents a pawn attack move in chess.
    Move.PawnEnPassantAttack
    The PawnEnPassantAttack class represents a special pawn attack move called "en passant" in chess.
    Move.PawnJump
    The PawnJump class represents a pawn move where a pawn advances two squares from its starting position.
    Move.PawnMove
    The PawnMove class represents a basic pawn move in chess.
    Move.PawnPromotion
    The PawnPromotion class represents a special move in chess.
    Move.QueenSideCastleMove
    The QueenSideCastleMove class represents a move for queen-side castling in chess.
    MovePool
    The MovePool class provides object pooling for Move instances to reduce garbage collection pressure and improve performance during chess engine search operations.
    MoveStatus
    The MoveStatus enum represents the possible outcomes of a chess move execution.
    MoveStrategy
    The MoveStrategy interface defines a contract for AI move selection algorithms used in chess gameplay.
    MoveTransition
    The MoveTransition class represents a transition between two chess board states resulting from a specific move.
    MoveUtils
    The MoveUtils class is a utility class that provides various helper methods related to chess moves and calculations.
    MoveUtils.Line
    The Line class represents a sequence of integer coordinates forming a line on the chess board.
    OpeningGameEvaluator
    The OpeningGameEvaluator class provides specialized board evaluation for opening positions in chess.
    Pawn
    The Pawn class represents a pawn chess piece with its unique movement and capture rules.
    Piece
    The `Piece` class represents a piece on the board in a game of chess.
    Piece.PieceType
    The PieceType enum defines the types of chess pieces and their associated values.
    PieceUtils
    The PieceUtils class provides utility methods for creating and accessing pre-computed instances of moved chess pieces.
    Player
    The Player class represents an abstract chess player, providing the foundation for player-specific operations and game state management.
    Queen
    The Queen class represents a queen chess piece, the most powerful piece on the board.
    Rook
    The Rook class represents a rook chess piece.
    StaticExchangeEvaluator
    The StaticExchangeEvaluator class implements Static Exchange Evaluation (SEE) for accurate assessment of capture sequences in chess positions.
    Table
    The Table class represents the main user interface for the Capstone chess engine.
    Table.AIThinkTank
    The AIThinkTank class is an asynchronous worker responsible for AI move calculation and execution.
    Table.BoardDirection
    The BoardDirection enumeration represents the two possible directions of the chess board display.
    Table.MoveLog
    The MoveLog class represents a log of moves made during a chess game.
    Table.PlayerType
    The PlayerType enumeration represents the types of players in the chess game.
    Table.TableGameAIWatcher
    The TableGameAIWatcher class observes changes in the game state and triggers AI actions or displays game-over messages based on certain conditions.
    Tile
    The Tile class represents a single square on a chess board.
    Tile.EmptyTile
    The EmptyTile class represents an empty tile on a chess board.
    Tile.OccupiedTile
    The OccupiedTile class represents a tile on a chess board that contains a piece.
    TranspositionTable
    The TranspositionTable class provides a hash table implementation for storing previously evaluated chess positions during search operations.
    TranspositionTable.Entry
    The Entry class represents a single record in the transposition table containing all necessary information about a previously evaluated chess position.
    WhitePlayer
    The WhitePlayer class represents a player controlling the white pieces in a chess game.
    ZobristHashing
    The ZobristHashing class implements the Zobrist hashing algorithm for chess positions.
